{
  "text": "The proliferation potential of NK cells isolated from cancer patients may be similar to that of NK cells from healthy donors, reassuring about the feasibility of manufacturing autologous NKcell products. Although autologous NK cells persist in vivo for at least 1 week after infusion, they express lower levels of NKG2D, a key activating receptor, and may necessitate in vitro re-activation with IL-2 to lyse tumor targets [CITATION_1] .",
